how do you get your team to align and follow with your metrics? Any challenges there,

00:58:59.040 --> 00:59:03.040
or are team senior leaders more aligned with data analytics lately?

00:59:03.520 --> 00:59:13.760
Well, I work in the best place for that, in the NBA, at least. Analytics and data scientists

00:59:13.760 --> 00:59:19.040
are highly respected in our organization. They are always asking about modeling, and I think

00:59:19.840 --> 00:59:27.840
it's incredible that this level of understanding exists throughout the organization. It's not just

00:59:27.840 --> 00:59:33.120
at the top. Even scouts are asking about the different statistical techniques and modeling,

00:59:33.760 --> 00:59:39.600
because they're incorporating it as shortcuts to what they know to look for.

00:59:41.840 --> 00:59:49.919
You continuously get more and more benefits from actually having a top-down understanding

00:59:49.919 --> 00:59:58.560
within your organization about analytics and metrics, like what's useful, what's not.

00:59:58.560 --> 01:00:10.959
It cuts down your search time to insight by an incredible amount. It's so very useful,

01:00:10.959 --> 01:00:16.320
and everybody should be doing it, and I'm very grateful to be in a position to do that.

01:00:16.479 --> 01:00:21.520
Everybody should be doing it, and I'm very grateful to be in a place where it is respected

01:00:21.520 --> 01:00:31.840
